        {
            "description": "Blown: a slide-flute waveguide after Cook-s STK flute. Breath pressure drives a jet delay (half the bore) into a cubic jet nonlinearity x(x^2-1); the bore is a delay loop closed by an inverting one-pole reflection filter, as at an open pipe end. Pitch is whatever frequency the loop decides to oscillate at, which is why the bore length carries an empirical correction."
